creator: Walter De la Mare
description:
LibriVox recording of Collected Poems 1901-1918 by Walter De la Mare.

Read in English by Claire Schreuder; Rebecca Braunert-Plunkett; Mary in Arkansas; Brett G. Hirsch; Ellen Preckel; rookieblue; Lucretia B.; Halle Kill; Mary Haynes; Phil Schempf; elisecandel; Anusha Iyer; Marmalade Hanna; Amy Koenig; Seanna Carey; sdaeley17; gribuongiorne; Greg Giordano; Gman; and Larry Wilson.

Early poems written by Walter de la Mare. de la Mare is best remembered for his works for children. This collection includes:

Poems: 1906
The Listeners: 1914
Motley: 1918
Songs of Childhood: 1901

(Summary by MaryAnn)

For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording.

For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.

M4B Format Available
